[SOBS]

258
00:17:20,952 --> 00:17:22,476
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING]

259
00:17:22,606 --> 00:17:23,651
[BOTH BREATHE HEAVILY]

260
00:17:23,781 --> 00:17:25,174
BOYD: I got it. I got it.

261
00:17:25,827 --> 00:17:26,697
JADE: That's it.

262
00:17:52,332 --> 00:17:54,943
I'm gonna go check on Tabitha
and the kids.

263
00:17:56,466 --> 00:17:57,989
I'm good.
JADE: Okay.

264
00:18:02,081 --> 00:18:03,169
ELLIS: Dad.

265
00:18:06,868 --> 00:18:08,261
I'm gonna need some help.

266
00:18:09,784 --> 00:18:10,785
Hey.

267
00:18:11,829 --> 00:18:12,874
Yeah, okay.

268
00:18:13,744 --> 00:18:14,832
Okay.

269
00:18:39,379 --> 00:18:41,163
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

270
00:18:41,250 --> 00:18:42,338
JADE: Watch your step.

271
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:44,558
BOYD: All right.

272
00:18:44,732 --> 00:18:46,037
[GRUNTS]

273
00:18:46,168 --> 00:18:47,126
It's okay.

274
00:18:47,996 --> 00:18:50,216
[GRUNTS, BREATHES HEAVILY]

275
00:18:53,871 --> 00:18:55,482
All right.
Let me get the door open.

276
00:18:58,354 --> 00:18:59,399
You good?

277
00:18:59,529 --> 00:19:01,052
All the way to the end.

278
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:04,012
Yep.

279
00:19:06,667 --> 00:19:07,885
[GRUNTS]

280
00:19:17,417 --> 00:19:19,810
We need to clean him up before
Tabitha and the kids see him.

281
00:19:22,552 --> 00:19:23,553
BOYD: Yeah.

282
00:19:28,341 --> 00:19:30,212
"Knowledge comes at a cost."

283
00:19:33,607 --> 00:19:35,261
The fuck does that even mean?

284
00:19:38,699 --> 00:19:39,874
We need to talk.

285
00:19:50,841 --> 00:19:51,842
Sara.

286
00:19:53,627 --> 00:19:54,671
Sara, what's...

287
00:19:55,803 --> 00:19:57,021
What's going on?

288
00:19:58,458 --> 00:20:01,156
They found Jim
in the barn this morning.

289
00:20:05,595 --> 00:20:06,727
Is he, um...

290
00:20:12,428 --> 00:20:13,255
Uh...

291
00:20:14,169 --> 00:20:15,344
Um...

292
00:20:16,432 --> 00:20:19,522
I'm gonna need you
to head back up to the clinic.

293
00:20:20,306 --> 00:20:22,351
But you said
we'd get new glasses.

294
00:20:24,310 --> 00:20:25,876
Are you going
to the storage room?

295
00:20:27,530 --> 00:20:28,488
Yeah.

296
00:20:29,532 --> 00:20:30,533
I can take her.

297
00:20:32,448 --> 00:20:35,582
No.
You're Sophia, right?

298
00:20:36,191 --> 00:20:38,193
I'm Sara.
I used to work at the diner.

299
00:20:38,280 --> 00:20:40,108
I know where
all the good stuff is.

300
00:20:44,895 --> 00:20:46,593
Okay, okay. Yeah.

301
00:20:48,290 --> 00:20:49,857
I know you two were close.

302
00:20:50,901 --> 00:20:51,989
I'm sorry.

303
00:20:53,904 --> 00:20:56,342
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

304
00:20:59,083 --> 00:21:00,128
SARA: Come on.

305
00:21:11,661 --> 00:21:12,967
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

306
00:21:14,229 --> 00:21:15,404
JADE: The children...

307
00:21:16,492 --> 00:21:21,454
The seven kids,
they kept saying this word
over and over again.

308
00:21:22,368 --> 00:21:23,630
Anghkooey.

309
00:21:24,413 --> 00:21:25,414
BOYD: Okay.

310
00:21:26,589 --> 00:21:31,551
When we played
the song at the tree,
it was like something unlocked.

311
00:21:32,203 --> 00:21:33,640
And we finally understood.

312
00:21:34,293 --> 00:21:35,294
Anghkooey.

313
00:21:36,599 --> 00:21:38,297
It means "remember."

314
00:21:39,994 --> 00:21:41,300
And we did.

315
00:21:44,172 --> 00:21:46,305
"Knowledge comes at a cost"?

316
00:21:47,828 --> 00:21:49,308
That's why they wrote it.

317
00:21:51,701 --> 00:21:53,442
It killed Jim because of us.

318
00:21:55,096 --> 00:21:57,925
"If we push too hard,
something would push back."

319
00:21:59,579 --> 00:22:00,580
What's that?

320
00:22:00,971 --> 00:22:03,322
Something Sara said
once we were out in the woods.

321
00:22:04,627 --> 00:22:07,935
Her brother, he had a theory
about this place.

322
00:22:08,022 --> 00:22:10,633
He didn't think looking
for answers was a good idea.

323
00:22:10,764 --> 00:22:11,852
[EXHALES]

324
00:22:13,723 --> 00:22:14,942
So what do we do now?

325
00:22:17,553 --> 00:22:20,730
Assuming you're right, that you
and Tabitha have been
coming back here

326
00:22:20,817 --> 00:22:22,297
over and over and over,

327
00:22:22,384 --> 00:22:25,256
that these kids keep calling you
back to help them,

328
00:22:25,344 --> 00:22:26,649
how do we do it?

329
00:22:28,216 --> 00:22:33,221
I mean, how do you even
begin to save something
that's... already dead?

330
00:22:33,874 --> 00:22:34,962
I don't know.

331
00:22:36,833 --> 00:22:38,182
I'm working on it.

332
00:22:38,835 --> 00:22:39,967
Yeah.

333
00:22:40,054 --> 00:22:41,142
Work harder.

334
00:22:44,493 --> 00:22:45,451
Come on.

335
00:22:52,936 --> 00:22:54,285
[DOOR SHUTTING]

336
00:23:00,466 --> 00:23:01,380
[DOOR SHUTTING]

337
00:23:02,555 --> 00:23:03,904
SARA: Give me a second.
Mm-hmm.

338
00:23:09,083 --> 00:23:10,084
Hey.

339
00:23:12,913 --> 00:23:14,044
Are you all right?

340
00:23:14,523 --> 00:23:15,742
We're not friends.

341
00:23:17,483 --> 00:23:19,267
Don't talk to me
like we're friends.

342
00:23:22,401 --> 00:23:23,402
Okay.

343
00:23:28,232 --> 00:23:29,364
It's right through here.

344
00:23:30,104 --> 00:23:31,322
Come on.

345
00:23:39,548 --> 00:23:42,029
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

346
00:23:54,302 --> 00:23:55,390
Ethan?

347
00:24:32,122 --> 00:24:33,123
Julie?

348
00:24:37,867 --> 00:24:38,912
Where's my mom?

349
00:24:39,042 --> 00:24:40,174
Uh...

350
00:24:40,740 --> 00:24:44,395
She'll be back. She just had
to step out for a minute.

351
00:24:45,788 --> 00:24:47,094
Can I get you something?

352
00:24:47,181 --> 00:24:48,661
I'm going for a walk.

353
00:24:49,226 --> 00:24:51,228
I want someone to go with you.

354
00:24:52,447 --> 00:24:56,495
It's the middle of the day,
Donna. I'll be fine.
I just need to...

355
00:24:57,104 --> 00:24:58,061
Okay.

356
00:24:59,410 --> 00:25:00,499
Uh, Ethan's asleep.

357
00:25:01,587 --> 00:25:02,544
DONNA: Julie?

358
00:25:03,980 --> 00:25:08,507
If you need anything,
you just ask me, okay?

359
00:25:15,078 --> 00:25:21,041
[GRUNTS]

360
00:25:21,737 --> 00:25:22,738
Randall?

361
00:25:27,264 --> 00:25:28,439
Randall.

362
00:25:29,049 --> 00:25:30,267
What the hell do you want?

363
00:25:33,401 --> 00:25:34,576
Hey, what happened?

364
00:25:38,058 --> 00:25:40,103
My dad is... [CRIES]

365
00:25:43,498 --> 00:25:45,282
Jesus Christ.
JULIE: [CRIES]

366
00:25:47,458 --> 00:25:48,938
Hey, look, I'm sorry.

367
00:25:49,025 --> 00:25:50,244
No, don't, don't.

368
00:25:52,594 --> 00:25:53,900
I need your help.

369
00:25:57,033 --> 00:25:58,165
Yeah, okay.

370
00:25:59,122 --> 00:26:01,081
I need you to come back
to the ruins with me.

371
00:26:01,864 --> 00:26:02,865
Why?

372
00:26:04,084 --> 00:26:05,389
Because I'm gonna save him.

373
00:26:14,137 --> 00:26:15,138
RANDALL: Julie.

374
00:26:16,792 --> 00:26:19,665
[SCUBS VIGOROUSLY]

375
00:26:22,493 --> 00:26:26,759
TABITHA:
[BREATHES HEAVILY, CRIES]

376
00:26:26,889 --> 00:26:28,151
[DOOR OPENING]

377
00:26:28,282 --> 00:26:31,894
TABITHA: [BREATHING HEAVILY]

378
00:26:33,287 --> 00:26:34,331
Tabitha.

379
00:26:37,987 --> 00:26:39,902
Get out.
No, listen, please. I just--

380
00:26:39,989 --> 00:26:40,903
I said get out!

381
00:26:43,993 --> 00:26:45,429
This means it's real.

382
00:26:47,518 --> 00:26:48,389
The memories.

383
00:26:49,303 --> 00:26:50,696
Everything they showed us.

384
00:26:53,002 --> 00:26:54,003
It's real.

385
00:26:55,004 --> 00:26:55,918
It is real.

386
00:27:00,009 --> 00:27:01,271
I don't give a shit.

387
00:27:01,968 --> 00:27:04,144
Do you understand?
I don't fucking care.

388
00:27:05,145 --> 00:27:07,364
Look, I can't even imagine
what you're going through.

389
00:27:08,322 --> 00:27:11,107
I know you don't
want to hear this right now,
but what they did...

390
00:27:11,281 --> 00:27:13,196
this message...
[SCRUBBING CONTINUES]

391
00:27:14,981 --> 00:27:17,592
I think they're doing it
to stop us from digging further.

392
00:27:18,201 --> 00:27:20,116
They're trying
to make us afraid.

393
00:27:20,726 --> 00:27:21,727
Well, then it worked.

394
00:27:26,819 --> 00:27:28,342
Because I'm fucking terrified.

395
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:32,868
My husband's dead.

396
00:27:34,609 --> 00:27:35,784
Do you understand?

397
00:27:36,655 --> 00:27:37,699
My husband's dead.

398
00:27:39,396 --> 00:27:41,660
You have to think
about your children now.

399
00:27:42,225 --> 00:27:43,226
[SCOFFS]

400
00:27:45,751 --> 00:27:46,882
You know what?

401
00:27:47,578 --> 00:27:48,623
Fuck you.

402
00:27:50,146 --> 00:27:51,191
Fuck you.

403
00:27:52,366 --> 00:27:53,802
What do you know, huh?

404
00:27:53,889 --> 00:27:55,282
What do you know?

405
00:27:55,935 --> 00:27:59,634
Do you want to go back
to The Bottle Tree
and play your stupid violin?

406
00:28:01,941 --> 00:28:03,551
Because you got nothing to lose.

407
00:28:05,205 --> 00:28:08,034
Because you don't give a shit
about anybody but yourself.

408
00:28:10,601 --> 00:28:12,081
That is not true.

409
00:28:15,955 --> 00:28:17,304
It should have been you...

410
00:28:19,741 --> 00:28:21,612
hanging from the fucking rafter.

411
00:28:23,614 --> 00:28:24,920
It should have been you.

412
00:28:45,375 --> 00:28:46,246
Fuck it.

413
00:28:46,812 --> 00:28:49,118
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

414
00:29:08,094 --> 00:29:10,574
[ENGINE STARTS]

415
00:29:11,793 --> 00:29:12,794
Hey!

416
00:29:13,752 --> 00:29:14,796
Fuck.

417
00:29:14,883 --> 00:29:16,450
Hey, hey, hey!

418
00:29:16,972 --> 00:29:18,191
Turn it off.

419
00:29:18,757 --> 00:29:19,758
Fuck!

420
00:29:20,671 --> 00:29:21,847
Turn off the engine

421
00:29:21,934 --> 00:29:23,457
and get out of the ambulance.
No.

422
00:29:24,545 --> 00:29:25,720
No.Hey.

423
00:29:26,765 --> 00:29:28,810
Are you insane?
Get the fuck out
of the ambulance.

424
00:29:28,897 --> 00:29:30,769
You want to go for a ride?
I'm coming with you.

425
00:29:33,075 --> 00:29:34,903
Jesus Christ.
KRISTI:
It's okay. It's okay.

426
00:29:34,990 --> 00:29:36,252
Come out, Kristi.
KRISTI: It's okay.

427
00:29:37,297 --> 00:29:38,341
Fine.

428
00:29:40,430 --> 00:29:42,258
Hey! Stop!

429
00:29:45,653 --> 00:29:47,046
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

430
00:29:50,005 --> 00:29:50,876
Kenny.

431
00:29:53,574 --> 00:29:55,619
I heard about Jim.

432
00:29:58,709 --> 00:29:59,754
Yeah.

433
00:30:01,190 --> 00:30:03,627
They left us a message
this time. That's new.

434
00:30:05,020 --> 00:30:06,848
Yeah, but Jade
has a theory about that.

435
00:30:08,371 --> 00:30:09,938
Sure, everybody's got a theory.

436
00:30:10,678 --> 00:30:11,984
No, there might be
something to this one.

437
00:30:13,899 --> 00:30:15,117
Boyd! [BREATHES HEAVILY]

438
00:30:15,291 --> 00:30:16,336
Kristi's in trouble.

439
00:30:16,945 --> 00:30:18,642
What?
Acosta took the ambulance.

440
00:30:18,729 --> 00:30:19,818
She's got Kristi inside.

441
00:30:29,610 --> 00:30:30,959
A tad big.

442
00:30:31,699 --> 00:30:34,136
Okay. Um..

443
00:30:36,617 --> 00:30:38,314
Nope, those do not work.
[CHUCKLES]

444
00:30:45,017 --> 00:30:46,148
How about these?

445
00:30:46,888 --> 00:30:48,020
Those look good.

446
00:30:50,979 --> 00:30:51,980
SOPHIA: So, um...

447
00:30:52,981 --> 00:30:56,376
It's so sad.
All these things... they...

448
00:30:57,464 --> 00:30:59,205
they belong to people
that were trapped here?

449
00:31:01,860 --> 00:31:02,730
Yeah.

450
00:31:06,081 --> 00:31:07,778
I wonder who these belonged to.

451
00:31:09,041 --> 00:31:11,739
Um... It's kind of nice,
though. I mean,

452
00:31:11,826 --> 00:31:14,437
there's a part of them
that's still here,

453
00:31:15,482 --> 00:31:17,832
a part that's... not forgotten.

454
00:31:19,529 --> 00:31:21,618
I've never really thought
of it that way.

455
00:31:31,890 --> 00:31:33,717
What happened
this morning to that man?

456
00:31:35,806 --> 00:31:37,591
Does that sort of thing
happen a lot?

457
00:31:39,375 --> 00:31:40,637
It never used to.

458
00:31:41,290 --> 00:31:44,685
For a long time after Boyd
found the talismans,
things were...

459
00:31:46,339 --> 00:31:48,732
It happens a lot more often now.

460
00:31:53,346 --> 00:31:55,957
I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have said that.

461
00:31:57,219 --> 00:32:00,266
It's okay. It's important
to be honest about things. Um...

462
00:32:01,441 --> 00:32:03,399
My dad used to always say that.

463
00:32:07,969 --> 00:32:09,362
Do you have family here?

464
00:32:11,538 --> 00:32:12,582
No.

465
00:32:13,844 --> 00:32:14,976
Not anymore.

466
00:32:17,109 --> 00:32:18,023
[SIGHS]

467
00:32:21,852 --> 00:32:23,419
Uh...
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

468
00:32:23,550 --> 00:32:25,856
You must be hungry.
We should get some food.

469
00:32:26,857 --> 00:32:28,816
Yeah, I am. I'm starving.

470
00:32:30,470 --> 00:32:31,514
Come on.

471
00:32:46,660 --> 00:32:48,488
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

472
00:32:48,967 --> 00:32:49,837
[SIGHS]

473
00:32:51,534 --> 00:32:53,362
[CAR APPROACHING]

474
00:32:53,449 --> 00:32:54,624
What the fuck?

475
00:33:02,197 --> 00:33:03,677
Here they come.
What?

476
00:33:05,070 --> 00:33:06,071
Hey!

477
00:33:06,158 --> 00:33:07,681
No, wait. Don't go!

478
00:33:10,597 --> 00:33:11,598
What's going on?

479
00:33:11,685 --> 00:33:13,469
Acosta's got Kristi
in the ambulance.

480
00:33:14,905 --> 00:33:16,342
Where the fuck are they going?

481
00:33:21,303 --> 00:33:23,131
BOYD: God damn, Acosta.
DONNA: What the hell?

482
00:33:23,218 --> 00:33:24,176
BOYD: All right.

483
00:33:38,277 --> 00:33:40,192
So everyone says
there's no way out, right?

484
00:33:40,279 --> 00:33:41,497
You just go round and round?

485
00:33:41,584 --> 00:33:42,498
Well, I didn't.

486
00:33:43,021 --> 00:33:44,761
The night I got here,
we drove in,

487
00:33:44,848 --> 00:33:46,763
we stopped in the road,
and then everything just...

488
00:33:47,286 --> 00:33:50,506
It all fucking exploded,
and then I took
all of you at your word.

489
00:33:51,116 --> 00:33:52,987
Why should I believe
a single thing you people say?

490
00:33:54,989 --> 00:33:56,338
Look, is this about Elgin?

491
00:33:57,252 --> 00:33:58,384
Look, you need to understand--

492
00:33:58,558 --> 00:34:00,038
No, I don't need
to understand shit, all right?

493
00:34:00,908 --> 00:34:03,737
Fuck. You're a doctor.
You're supposed to help people.

494
00:34:03,824 --> 00:34:04,955
You really okay with that?

495
00:34:05,043 --> 00:34:06,827
Oh, I'm not okay
with any of this.

496
00:34:07,393 --> 00:34:08,611
And you're a cop.

497
00:34:08,698 --> 00:34:10,570
And what you're doing
is gonna get people hurt.

498
00:34:10,657 --> 00:34:11,788
No.

499
00:34:11,875 --> 00:34:13,529
What I'm doing is getting out.

500
00:34:13,964 --> 00:34:15,183
Right fucking now.

501
00:34:17,272 --> 00:34:19,231
[CAR ACCELERATES]

502
00:34:20,101 --> 00:34:21,102
RANDALL: Julie.

503
00:34:23,061 --> 00:34:24,671
Look, Julie, slow down.

504
00:34:24,758 --> 00:34:25,802
Slow down.

505
00:34:27,021 --> 00:34:29,154
So what? We step inside
the ruins and then what?

506
00:34:29,589 --> 00:34:30,938
We walk through time?

507
00:34:31,547 --> 00:34:33,506
Ethan called it Storywalking.
Okay, great.

508
00:34:33,593 --> 00:34:35,595
That doesn't make it
any fucking better. Julie, stop.

509
00:34:35,682 --> 00:34:36,900
You can't--
What?

510
00:34:39,251 --> 00:34:40,643
Like, what happened?

511
00:34:41,514 --> 00:34:42,776
With your dad?

512
00:34:44,430 --> 00:34:46,084
What you're going
through right now.

513
00:34:47,128 --> 00:34:49,652
Hey, you gotta take a breath.

514
00:34:51,480 --> 00:34:52,568
And what?

515
00:34:54,440 --> 00:34:56,572
What do I do then, huh?

516
00:34:57,747 --> 00:35:01,316
I am telling you,
when I walked into those ruins,
I went somewhere.

517
00:35:02,100 --> 00:35:03,362
Okay?

518
00:35:03,449 --> 00:35:05,973
If I did it once,
I can do it again.

519
00:35:07,061 --> 00:35:08,889
Even if there is
the slightest fucking chance,

520
00:35:08,976 --> 00:35:10,543
I have to try.

521
00:35:11,500 --> 00:35:12,545
Please.

522
00:35:18,116 --> 00:35:19,595
Just tell me
what you need me to do.

523
00:35:46,709 --> 00:35:48,798
[SOBS]

524
00:36:11,560 --> 00:36:13,171
Why didn't you come home, Jim?

525
00:36:14,259 --> 00:36:15,303
[SNIFFS]

526
00:36:16,435 --> 00:36:18,132
I was waiting for you.

527
00:36:20,395 --> 00:36:21,962
Why didn't you come home?

528
00:36:26,619 --> 00:36:28,621
[SOBS] I'm so angry at you.

529
00:36:32,712 --> 00:36:36,237
All night I thought about
what I wish I said to you
in the woods.

530
00:36:40,720 --> 00:36:42,374
I thought about the fact that...

531
00:36:45,812 --> 00:36:49,207
I've loved you since
the first moment I saw you.

532
00:36:56,953 --> 00:37:00,218
There's been so much fighting,
so much pain.

533
00:37:04,134 --> 00:37:05,614
You were still my person.

534
00:37:10,793 --> 00:37:12,317
You're my everything.

535
00:37:12,404 --> 00:37:14,710
I'm so afraid
you didn't know that.

536
00:37:22,196 --> 00:37:24,503
How am I supposed to do this
without you here?

537
00:37:33,207 --> 00:37:35,209
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING]

538
00:37:35,340 --> 00:37:36,558
We're gonna be okay.

539
00:37:40,083 --> 00:37:41,302
Julie and Ethan.

540
00:37:44,131 --> 00:37:45,393
I don't know how...

541
00:37:47,482 --> 00:37:50,746
but I'm going to find a way
to take care of them,
to keep them safe.

542
00:37:53,053 --> 00:37:54,533
You don't have to be afraid.

543
00:38:06,371 --> 00:38:07,633
I love you, Jim.

544
00:38:14,161 --> 00:38:15,380
Goodbye.

545
00:38:22,125 --> 00:38:23,866
BOYD: Here we go.
Hey, get out of the way.

546
00:38:25,781 --> 00:38:27,000
Hey, stop!

547
00:38:30,612 --> 00:38:31,700
Okay, slow down.

548
00:38:32,397 --> 00:38:33,354
BOYD: Stop!

549
00:38:34,747 --> 00:38:36,836
Slow down. Slow down.
Stop! Stop!

550
00:38:39,360 --> 00:38:41,362
[OVERLAPPING SHOUTING]

551
00:38:44,191 --> 00:38:45,932
Fuck. You're going way
too fucking fast right now.

552
00:38:46,019 --> 00:38:48,195
We've been through town
twice already.
What more do you need to see?

553
00:38:48,326 --> 00:38:50,240
There's got to be a way.
I'm not just going to sit around

554
00:38:50,328 --> 00:38:52,068
and wait for those things
to pick us off one by one.

555
00:38:52,155 --> 00:38:54,767
You guys just hang
your rocks at night.
You pretend you're safe,

556
00:38:54,854 --> 00:38:57,552
thinking that Sheriff Boyd
is going to what,
somehow save you?

557
00:38:58,118 --> 00:39:00,816
Let me tell you something,
Boyd... Boyd doesn't know
what he's doing.

558
00:39:00,903 --> 00:39:02,905
None of you people know
what the fuck you're doing.

559
00:39:03,036 --> 00:39:05,255
But you do.
Yeah, well, at least I'm trying.

560
00:39:07,606 --> 00:39:08,868
That was a lot faster.

561
00:39:08,955 --> 00:39:10,260
Yeah, that's the pattern.

562
00:39:11,131 --> 00:39:14,090
She's looking for a way out.
She's just going to get
more and more...

563
00:39:14,526 --> 00:39:15,570
What do we do?

564
00:39:16,005 --> 00:39:16,919
Get the strip.

565
00:39:17,616 --> 00:39:18,573
Yeah.

566
00:39:21,533 --> 00:39:22,360
Victor?

567
00:39:25,232 --> 00:39:26,146
You in here?

568
00:39:38,027 --> 00:39:39,551
VICTOR:
You shouldn't have come here.

569
00:39:47,733 --> 00:39:48,734
Hey.

570
00:39:49,474 --> 00:39:50,475
I...

571
00:39:51,040 --> 00:39:53,956
I heard about Jim. I'm sorry.

572
00:39:55,393 --> 00:39:57,351
You shouldn't have come here.

573
00:39:57,438 --> 00:39:59,440
You should never
have come to this place.

574
00:40:03,836 --> 00:40:06,229
Have you gone to see Ethan yet?

575
00:40:06,316 --> 00:40:07,622
No.
No? Okay.

576
00:40:07,709 --> 00:40:08,710
No.

577
00:40:09,102 --> 00:40:09,972
I can't.

578
00:40:10,799 --> 00:40:11,670
You can't?

579
00:40:12,322 --> 00:40:15,064
Well, Victor,
he's your friend, and...

580
00:40:16,544 --> 00:40:18,807
he needs you,
so when you're ready...

581
00:40:19,765 --> 00:40:21,375
Those words on the wall...

582
00:40:21,462 --> 00:40:23,159
The words, sure, yeah.
Yeah.

583
00:40:23,246 --> 00:40:25,858
You see, this place
takes everything good.

584
00:40:25,945 --> 00:40:29,688
It takes everything...
everything good away.

585
00:40:30,515 --> 00:40:32,865
And then what
if it takes you next?

586
00:40:34,519 --> 00:40:36,825
Me? Well,
I'm not going anywhere.

587
00:40:37,783 --> 00:40:38,697
No, no.

588
00:40:38,827 --> 00:40:40,699
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

589
00:40:40,829 --> 00:40:42,440
You don't know that.

590
00:40:42,527 --> 00:40:43,658
No.

591
00:40:43,745 --> 00:40:45,834
You don't know that.
Okay.

592
00:40:45,921 --> 00:40:47,793
VICTOR: So you just
shouldn't have come.

593
00:40:47,923 --> 00:40:49,447
You shouldn't...

594
00:40:49,664 --> 00:40:52,275
You shouldn't have
come to this place.

595
00:40:52,362 --> 00:40:53,712
You should never have c...

596
00:40:53,799 --> 00:40:55,540
Hey, hey, hey, listen.

597
00:40:55,627 --> 00:40:59,674
No one should have
come to this place.

598
00:40:59,761 --> 00:41:01,676
Hey, none of us.

599
00:41:02,677 --> 00:41:04,592
But, you know, we're here.

600
00:41:05,332 --> 00:41:07,682
You and me, and we're together.

601
00:41:07,769 --> 00:41:10,076
I'll take that
any day of the week,

602
00:41:10,163 --> 00:41:13,296
no matter what
gets written on the walls.

603
00:41:13,383 --> 00:41:14,428
We...

604
00:41:15,037 --> 00:41:16,996
We face this together.

605
00:41:17,692 --> 00:41:19,433
Okay? Okay?

606
00:41:31,445 --> 00:41:34,013
So you just... walk inside?

607
00:41:35,710 --> 00:41:36,711
Yeah.

608
00:41:38,017 --> 00:41:39,322
And then what?

609
00:41:40,062 --> 00:41:41,237
Then I find my dad.

610
00:41:46,373 --> 00:41:48,114
You go first.
What?

611
00:41:48,680 --> 00:41:50,595
Just... walk inside.

612
00:41:50,682 --> 00:41:53,075
Why?
Will you just do it, please?

613
00:41:56,949 --> 00:41:59,081
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

614
00:42:13,008 --> 00:42:14,009
What's supposed to happen?

615
00:42:14,836 --> 00:42:15,663
Nothing.

616
00:42:17,491 --> 00:42:19,362
I... I just had to make sure
that the same thing

617
00:42:19,449 --> 00:42:21,495
wasn't gonna happen to you
when you come in to get me.

618
00:42:22,322 --> 00:42:23,497
Come back.

619
00:42:26,456 --> 00:42:27,501
Look, look.

620
00:42:28,850 --> 00:42:32,158
I need you to give me some time
before you pull me out.

621
00:42:32,637 --> 00:42:33,725
Okay?

622
00:42:34,334 --> 00:42:36,989
Even if it looks bad.
What do you mean
if it looks bad?

623
00:42:39,121 --> 00:42:40,688
Julie, what's gonna happen?

624
00:42:40,775 --> 00:42:42,734
Promise me. Please.

625
00:42:44,344 --> 00:42:45,737
Okay, fine.

626
00:42:45,824 --> 00:42:47,042
You have to promise.

627
00:42:48,957 --> 00:42:49,871
Promise!

628
00:42:49,958 --> 00:42:51,699
All right, yes. I promise.

629
00:42:51,786 --> 00:42:52,613
JULIE: Okay.

630
00:43:25,777 --> 00:43:29,128
[CREATURE 1 SCREAMING]

631
00:43:56,285 --> 00:43:58,244
[CREATURE 2 SCREAMING]

632
00:44:04,729 --> 00:44:05,599
Dad!

633
00:44:12,911 --> 00:44:14,782
BOYD: All right, you guys.
Get out of here. Go!

634
00:44:14,869 --> 00:44:16,088
Go! Go!

635
00:44:16,262 --> 00:44:20,832
[GUNSHOTS]

636
00:44:25,271 --> 00:44:26,228
Dad!

637
00:44:27,752 --> 00:44:30,668
[SCREAMS]

638
00:44:31,320 --> 00:44:33,496
[GRUNTS]

639
00:44:37,022 --> 00:44:38,153
Get off me!

640
00:44:38,240 --> 00:44:39,502
But I want to play.

641
00:44:39,589 --> 00:44:44,943
[GRUNTS]

642
00:44:47,510 --> 00:44:48,555
Come on, come on.

643
00:44:49,730 --> 00:44:50,600
Randall!

644
00:44:51,950 --> 00:44:53,342
Randall, pull me out!

645
00:44:53,429 --> 00:44:55,388
There's no one here to help you.

646
00:44:56,128 --> 00:44:56,998
No!

647
00:44:57,651 --> 00:44:59,479
[SCREAMS]

648
00:44:59,609 --> 00:45:01,742
[SCREAMS]

649
00:45:01,873 --> 00:45:05,006
[GRUNTS]

650
00:45:10,055 --> 00:45:12,884
[SCREAMS] No, no, no!

651
00:45:13,362 --> 00:45:15,321
Look at me. Look at me.
It's okay.

652
00:45:15,974 --> 00:45:17,802
I saw him. Oh, Randall.
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

653
00:45:17,889 --> 00:45:19,368
Oh, my god. I saw him.
You saw him.

654
00:45:19,499 --> 00:45:20,543
I saw him, but I couldn't--

655
00:45:20,630 --> 00:45:22,458
I have to go back!
No, no, no, stop.

656
00:45:22,545 --> 00:45:24,069
No, no, no.
Hey, stop, stop, stop.

657
00:45:24,417 --> 00:45:26,114
Oh, God! [SOBS]
I got you.

658
00:45:26,201 --> 00:45:27,463
I have to go back.

659
00:45:36,124 --> 00:45:37,082
Ethan?

660
00:45:38,474 --> 00:45:39,693
[KNOCKS]

661
00:45:40,346 --> 00:45:42,000
Ethan, can I come in?

662
00:45:44,263 --> 00:45:45,220
Ethan?

663
00:45:55,317 --> 00:45:56,318
Donna?

664
00:45:57,929 --> 00:45:59,147
Ethan's not up there.

665
00:45:59,234 --> 00:46:00,235
What?

666
00:46:00,322 --> 00:46:01,759
I was here the whole time.

667
00:46:03,282 --> 00:46:06,111
Ethan?
Tabitha, he was upstairs!

668
00:46:06,198 --> 00:46:07,155
Ethan!

669
00:46:13,683 --> 00:46:14,684
Ethan!

670
00:46:15,120 --> 00:46:16,077
[GRUNTS]

671
00:46:18,384 --> 00:46:19,820
All right. Got it?
KENNY: Yeah.

672
00:46:21,517 --> 00:46:22,736
Hey, she's gonna be okay.

673
00:46:25,478 --> 00:46:26,958
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

674
00:46:31,353 --> 00:46:32,354
My mom, she...

675
00:46:34,226 --> 00:46:35,662
She always believed in hell.

676
00:46:36,663 --> 00:46:38,012
But you know what I think?

677
00:46:38,752 --> 00:46:40,623
I think hell
is for people who think

678
00:46:40,710 --> 00:46:42,582
that they deserve to suffer,
and I don't.

679
00:46:43,670 --> 00:46:46,151
I am a good person,
and I don't deserve to be here.

680
00:46:46,716 --> 00:46:47,935
None of us deserve to be here.

681
00:46:48,022 --> 00:46:50,068
I don't know that. I don't.

682
00:46:50,155 --> 00:46:52,331
I don't know a single thing
about you people.

683
00:46:53,071 --> 00:46:55,508
And you know,
maybe the real reason
that you don't try harder

684
00:46:55,595 --> 00:46:58,206
is that deep down you think
that you deserve to be here.

685
00:46:58,816 --> 00:47:01,514
The real reason
we don't try harder
is because every time we do,

686
00:47:01,601 --> 00:47:02,907
somebody fucking dies.

687
00:47:03,472 --> 00:47:04,996
Do you know
how many people I've known

688
00:47:05,083 --> 00:47:07,389
who thought they knew
exactly what this place is?

689
00:47:07,912 --> 00:47:10,175
How many theories
I've listened to
on why we're all here?

690
00:47:10,262 --> 00:47:12,220
Or brilliant ideas
on how to get out?

691
00:47:12,612 --> 00:47:14,092
You want to know
what they all have in common?

692
00:47:14,832 --> 00:47:16,268
They're all fucking dead.

693
00:47:16,355 --> 00:47:18,487
There is no way out.
Do you understand that?

694
00:47:18,574 --> 00:47:19,706
No! Okay?!

695
00:47:20,272 --> 00:47:21,360
There's a way!

696
00:47:22,056 --> 00:47:24,667
There is a way!
There is always a way.

697
00:47:31,152 --> 00:47:32,023
Ethan.

698
00:47:40,770 --> 00:47:41,859
Okay, pull over.

699
00:47:46,515 --> 00:47:47,560
He's fine.

700
00:47:48,387 --> 00:47:50,650
He's a fucking kid
in the woods whose father
just died. Pull over!

701
00:47:59,920 --> 00:48:00,965
No, no, no.

702
00:48:02,053 --> 00:48:03,445
Hey, come on.
Marielle. Let's go.
Okay.

703
00:48:03,532 --> 00:48:04,882
Let's go, let's go.

704
00:48:04,969 --> 00:48:06,057
Fuck.

705
00:48:08,494 --> 00:48:09,538
KRISTI: Stop!

706
00:48:10,844 --> 00:48:13,803
[TIRES SCREECHING]

707
00:48:13,934 --> 00:48:14,935
Kristi!

708
00:48:16,763 --> 00:48:19,157
Are you okay?
BOYD: Hey, get the fuck
out of the car.

709
00:48:19,548 --> 00:48:21,159
Get the fuck out!

710
00:48:21,246 --> 00:48:22,812
KENNY: Hey, you good?
Yeah.

711
00:48:23,422 --> 00:48:26,033
What the fuck
is wrong with you, huh?

712
00:48:26,120 --> 00:48:28,253
You could've killed somebody,
you know that?

713
00:48:28,340 --> 00:48:30,168
Turn around.
ACOSTA: [GRUNTS]

714
00:48:30,255 --> 00:48:31,560
[HANDCUFFS CLATTER]

715
00:48:32,344 --> 00:48:34,824
Fucking driving like
a crazy fucking person out here.

716
00:48:34,912 --> 00:48:36,783
[HANDCUFFS FASTEN]

717
00:48:37,436 --> 00:48:39,568
Huh? Answer me!

718
00:48:39,655 --> 00:48:40,526
Boyd!

719
00:48:47,315 --> 00:48:50,449
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

720
00:48:50,536 --> 00:48:52,538
BOYD: Let's go. Let's go.

721
00:48:52,625 --> 00:48:54,105
Ethan.
What?

722
00:48:54,844 --> 00:48:56,716
Ethan, he was walking
on the road.

723
00:48:56,803 --> 00:48:57,978
BOYD: What?
Yeah.

724
00:50:00,475 --> 00:50:01,389
Dad?

725
00:50:04,784 --> 00:50:05,654
Ethan.

726
00:50:09,006 --> 00:50:10,616
JIM: [SIGHS]
ETHAN: [GRUNTS]

727
00:50:11,312 --> 00:50:13,010
God. Oh.

728
00:50:17,536 --> 00:50:18,580
What are you doing out here?

729
00:50:19,233 --> 00:50:20,495
I came to get the radio.

730
00:50:20,582 --> 00:50:21,627
[SIGHS]

731
00:50:25,892 --> 00:50:26,980
It's broken.

732
00:50:27,546 --> 00:50:29,591
I thought maybe
I could send Thomas a message.

733
00:50:31,115 --> 00:50:32,246
The real Thomas.

734
00:50:33,639 --> 00:50:36,903
That he should look for you
so you wouldn't be alone.

735
00:50:44,998 --> 00:50:46,043
What's wrong?

736
00:50:47,653 --> 00:50:48,741
Everything's okay.

737
00:50:50,873 --> 00:50:54,529
Do you remember
what I told you last time
we were here at the RV?

738
00:50:55,182 --> 00:50:56,662
That when bad things happen,

739
00:50:57,619 --> 00:51:00,796
we have to look after each other
and always do our best?

740
00:51:01,884 --> 00:51:02,929
That's right.

741
00:51:03,886 --> 00:51:05,758
And your mom and your sister...

742
00:51:06,846 --> 00:51:09,892
they need that from you now
more than ever.

743
00:51:12,678 --> 00:51:14,375
You're not staying, are you?

744
00:51:18,118 --> 00:51:19,424
I wish that I could.

745
00:51:24,385 --> 00:51:27,084
Dad... what's happening?

746
00:51:32,872 --> 00:51:35,092
I need you to do something
very important.

747
00:51:37,050 --> 00:51:40,793
The night we arrived
here and we crashed the RV
and we were trapped inside...

748
00:51:45,232 --> 00:51:46,451
you had a dream.

749
00:51:47,756 --> 00:51:50,368
Do you remember
what you dreamt about?

750
00:51:51,499 --> 00:51:52,805
The Lake of Tears?

751
00:51:54,023 --> 00:51:55,199
That's right.

752
00:51:56,287 --> 00:51:57,723
Do you know why?

753
00:52:01,030 --> 00:52:01,901
It's here.

754
00:52:02,902 --> 00:52:04,338
And I need you to find it.

755
00:52:06,079 --> 00:52:07,776
Why can't we find it together?

756
00:52:08,342 --> 00:52:09,778
TABITHA: Ethan![GASPS]

757
00:52:14,305 --> 00:52:15,306
TABITHA: Ethan!

758
00:52:19,353 --> 00:52:20,311
Dad?

759
00:52:21,703 --> 00:52:23,009
Dad, where are you?

760
00:52:23,618 --> 00:52:24,793
Ethan!
Dad, come back!

761
00:52:24,880 --> 00:52:26,839
Dad, please come back!
Ethan, Ethan!

762
00:52:28,710 --> 00:52:31,409
Baby, why are you here?
I was so worried.

763
00:52:31,496 --> 00:52:32,671
I saw Dad.

764
00:52:33,846 --> 00:52:34,803
He was right here.

765
00:52:36,892 --> 00:52:38,198
Oh, my baby.

766
00:52:48,643 --> 00:52:50,384
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

767
00:53:26,855 --> 00:53:28,596
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]
